{"HYO-":[{"def":"A prexif used in anatomy, and generally denoting connection with the hyoid bone or arch; as, hyoglossal, hyomandibular, hyomental, etc.","pos":""}],"HYOGANOIDEI":[{"def":"A division of ganoid fishes, including the gar pikes and bowfins.","pos":""}],"HYOGLOSSUS":[{"def":"A flat muscle on either side of the tongue, connecting it with the hyoid bone.","pos":""}],"HYOID":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to the bony or cartilaginous arch which supports the tongue.","pos":""}],"HYOMANDIBULAR":[{"def":"Pertaining both to the hyoidean arch and the mandible or lower jaw; as, the hyomandibular bone or cartilage, a segment of the hyoid arch which connects the lower jaw with the skull in fishes.","pos":""},{"def":"The hyomandibular bone or cartilage.","pos":""}],"HYOMENTAL":[{"def":"Between the hyoid bone and the lower jaw, pertaining to them; suprahyoid; submaxillary; as, the hyomental region of the front of the neck.","pos":""}],"HYOPASTRON":[{"def":"The second lateral plate in the plastron of turtles; -- called also hyosternum.","pos":""}],"HYOSCINE":[{"def":"An alkaloid found with hyoscyamine (with which it is also isomeric) in henbane, and extracted as a white, amorphous, semisolid substance.","pos":""}],"HYOSCYAMINE":[{"def":"An alkaloid found in henbane (Hyoscyamus niger), and regarded as its active principle.","pos":""}],"HYOSCYAMUS":[{"def":"A genus of poisonous plants of the Nightshade family; henbane.","pos":""},{"def":"The leaves of the black henbane (Hyoscyamus niger), used in neuralgic and pectorial troubles.","pos":""}],"HYOSTERNUM":[{"def":"See Hyoplastron.","pos":""}],"HYOSTYLIC":[{"def":"Having the mandible suspended by the hyomandibular, or upper part of the hyoid arch, as in fishes, instead of directly articulated with the skull as in mammals; -- said of the skull.","pos":""}]}